#: ../introduction.rst:78
msgid "System Requirements"
msgstr ""

#: ../introduction.rst:79
msgid "Video editing benefits from modern, multi-core CPUs with **fast clock speeds** (GHz), large amounts of memory, and fast hard disk drives. Basically, you want the best computer you can afford when video editing. Here are the **minimum system requirements**:"
msgstr ""

#: ../introduction.rst:84
msgid "TL;DR"
msgstr ""

#: ../introduction.rst:85
msgid "Most computers manufactured after 2017 will run OpenShot"
msgstr ""

#: ../introduction.rst:88
msgid "Minimum Specifications"
msgstr ""

#: ../introduction.rst:89
msgid "64-bit Operating System (*Linux, OS X, Chrome OS, Windows 7/8/10/11*)"
msgstr ""

#: ../introduction.rst:92
msgid "Multi-core processor with 64-bit support"
msgstr ""

#: ../introduction.rst:91
msgid "Minimum cores: 2 (*recommended: 6+ cores*)"
msgstr ""

#: ../introduction.rst:92
msgid "Minimum threads: 4 (*recommended: 6+ threads*)"
msgstr ""

#: ../introduction.rst:93
msgid "Minimum turbo clock speed: 2.7 Ghz (*recommended: 3.4+ Ghz*)"
msgstr ""

#: ../introduction.rst:94
msgid "4GB of RAM (*16+ GB recommended*)"
msgstr ""

#: ../introduction.rst:95
msgid "1 GB of hard-disk space for installation & usage (*recommended: 50+ GB available hard-disk space for media, videos, images, and storage*)"
msgstr ""

#: ../introduction.rst:96
msgid "Optional: Solid-state drive (SSD), if utilizing disk-caching add an additional 10GB of hard-disk space"
msgstr ""

